    "Regular follow-up visits.",
    "Histopathological examination to ensure complete removal.",
    "by an oral and maxillofacial surgeon or a pediatric dentist.",
    "Radiographic studies: panoramic X-rays or cone-beam CT, to confirm and visualize the cystic lesion and the presence of tooth-like structures (odontoma).",
    "Consultation with a pathologist for histopathological examination."
